                  <persName id="t18270712-29-person250">
                  THOMAS 
                  HUTTON
               <interp inst="t18270712-29-person250" type="surname" value="HUTTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270712-29-person250" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270712-29-person250" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to William Farrar, who <rs id="t18270712-29-viclabel178" type="occupation">keeps a Scotch warehouse</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-29-victim249 t18270712-29-viclabel178"></join>, at No. 56, <placeName id="t18270712-29-crimeloc179">Bread-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270712-29-crimeloc179" type="placeName" value="Bread-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270712-29-crimeloc179" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-29-off176 t18270712-29-crimeloc179"></join>. On the 11th of July I was in the warehouse, the door was ajar - I heard a noise, turned my head, and saw a hand just within the entrance of the door, but I could not see the person's face - the hand laid hold of a piece of holland, and took it out. I opened the door, and the man let the goods fall - I pursued, and merely lost sight of him for half a minute, as he turned the corner. I am sure I caught sight of the same man again - it was the prisoner; he was stopped in my sight - the holland is worth 21s. I saw him drop it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270712-29-person251">
                  THOMAS 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18270712-29-person251" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270712-29-person251" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270712-29-person251" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a porter. I heard the cry of Stop thief! at the corner of Bow-lane, Watling-street; I saw the prisoner running down Watling-street, and stopped him; Hutton and several others were pursuing him; he said, "It is nothing, only just a lark - let me go;" Hutton took him back.</p>
               <p>
            
